    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "```\n(15:50:41) antares79: pchote: how would you do that? spawn a camera where the actor was, or add some magic to the shroud/frozen actor layer?\n(15:50:53) pchote: magic to shroud\n(15:51:15) pchote: we could then use the same magic for revealing firing locations and getting rid of the camera actors\n(15:51:42) antares79: for super powers, you mean?\n(15:51:49) pchote: and scripts\n(15:51:59) pchote: creating a specific actor for each reveal range is dumb\n(15:52:16) pchote: it would be much nicer if maps and support powers could just say \"reveal shroud at X with radius R\"\n(15:53:56) pchote: easiest way is probably to add an abstraction\n(15:54:06) pchote: make it so shroud doesn't deal with actors directly, but some kind of shroud proxy\n(15:54:16) pchote: RevealsShroud then deals with manipulating the proxy for an actor\n(15:54:24) pchote: and scripts and superweapons can make their own proxies\n(15:54:42) pchote: we already kind of do that already\n(15:54:51) pchote: except instead of an explicit proxy we just pass around a reference to a list of cells\n```\n"
